wiki.content: “gameboy” is the seventh track from ROSÉ’s debut album, rosie. The lyrics continue from the album’s third track, “two years,” which reflects on ROSÉ’s struggle to move on from her ex, even after two years. She reveals that her inability to move on is that the boy who appeared to be a good guy only wanted to play with her feelings using the metaphor of a “game boy.” “gameboy” was first teased during an Instagram live session ROSÉ did with her producer, Teddy Park, co-founder and producer of her label in South Korea, THEBLACKLABEL.
